🧑‍🎓 STUDENT PORTAL
Domain: portal.yourdomain.com/student
Execution Domain: exam.yourdomain.com/session/{sessionId}

0️⃣ CORE PRINCIPLES
Student Portal must:
    • Motivate
    • Simplify
    • Never intimidate
    • Never expose raw system logic
    • Never show commercial licensing
    • Never query raw sessions
    • Always use summary documents
    • Replace “Score” with:
        ◦ Raw Score %
        ◦ Accuracy %
Score (absolute marks) must not appear as cumulative metric anywhere.

1️⃣ STUDENT PORTAL — COMPLETE MAP
Student Portal
│
├── Dashboard
├── My Tests
│    ├── Available
│    ├── In Progress
│    ├── Completed
│    └── Archived
│
├── Performance
│
├── Insights (L1+)
│
├── Discipline (L2+)
│
└── Profile & Settings

2️⃣ DASHBOARD (MOTIVATION-FIRST DESIGN)
Purpose:
Immediate clarity + confidence.
Data source:
    • studentYearMetrics
    • runs (filtered)
    • recent runAnalytics summary

🟢 L0 Dashboard
Top Banner (Motivational)
    • “Keep Building Momentum”
    • Dynamic message:
        ◦ “You improved Raw % by +6% in last 3 tests.”
        ◦ “Consistency is your strength this month.”

Core Cards
    • 📊 Avg Raw Score % (Last 5 Tests)
    • 🎯 Avg Accuracy %
    • 📝 Tests Attempted (Current Year)
    • ⏳ Upcoming Tests Count
    • 🏅 Batch Rank (Optional)
No cumulative “Score”.

🟡 L1 Adds
    • Phase Adherence %
    • Easy Neglect %
    • Hard Bias %
    • Time Misallocation %
    • Behavior Summary Tag
Example:
“You perform better when attempting Easy questions early.”
Neutral language only.

🔵 L2 Adds
    • Risk State Badge
    • Discipline Index
    • Controlled Mode Improvement Delta
    • Guess Probability Indicator
    • Mini Phase Compliance Trend
Badge example:
🟢 Stable
🟡 Improving
🔵 Building Discipline
Never show “Volatile” aggressively.

3️⃣ MY TESTS SECTION
Purpose:
Assignment management + execution gateway.

Tabs
    • Available
    • In Progress
    • Completed
    • Archived

AVAILABLE
Each Test Card Shows:
    • Test Name
    • Duration
    • Start Window
    • End Window
    • Mode Badge (simplified label)
    • “Start Test” Button
Start flow:
Backend → create session
→ Redirect to exam.yourdomain.com/session/{sessionId}
No test links in email.

IN PROGRESS
    • Resume Button
    • Time Remaining
    • Attempt Status

COMPLETED (CURRENT YEAR)
For each test:
Show:
    • Raw Score %
    • Accuracy %
    • Time Used
    • Rank in Batch (optional)
    • Completion Date
Buttons:
    • 🔍 View Solutions (preferred over download for speed)
    • 📥 Download PDF Summary (optional)

SOLUTION VIEW STRUCTURE
When student clicks View Solutions:
For each question:
    • Question Image
    • Correct Answer
    • Student Answer
    • Explanation (SolutionImageFile)
    • TutorialVideoLink (if exists)
    • SimulationLink (if exists)
Show links only if present.

ARCHIVED (PAST ACADEMIC YEAR)
Show:
    • Test Name
    • Raw %
    • Accuracy %
    • Date
Do NOT show:
    • Solution view
    • Solution download
    • TutorialVideoLink
    • SimulationLink
Reason:
Storage in COLD partition.
Only summary retained in Firestore.

4️⃣ PERFORMANCE SECTION
Purpose:
Longitudinal growth visualization.

🟢 L0
Per test:
    • Raw %
    • Accuracy %
    • Time Spent
    • Rank
Charts:
    • Raw % Trend
    • Accuracy % Trend
Two-line combo chart only.

🟡 L1 Adds
    • Phase Adherence Trend
    • Easy Neglect Frequency
    • Hard Bias Frequency
    • Topic Performance Breakdown
    • Time Allocation Chart

🔵 L2 Adds
    • Risk State Timeline
    • Discipline Index Trend
    • Guess Rate Trend
    • MinTime Violation %
    • MaxTime Violation % (Hard Mode)
    • Controlled Mode Comparison
All precomputed.

5️⃣ INSIGHTS (L1+)
Purpose:
Reflective intelligence.
Show:
    • Most Frequent Behavior Pattern
    • Topic Weakness Summary
    • Late-Phase Drop Indicator
    • Rushed Pattern Frequency
    • Skip Burst Indicator
Tone:
Constructive.
Example:
“You gain highest accuracy when pacing evenly.”
No red alert styling.

6️⃣ DISCIPLINE (L2+)
Purpose:
Execution maturity tracking.
Display:
    • Discipline Index (0–100)
    • Phase Compliance %
    • Controlled Mode Improvement %
    • Overstay Frequency
    • Guess Probability Cluster
Mini progress bars.
No heavy charts.

7️⃣ PROFILE & SETTINGS
    • Name
    • Email
    • Batch
    • Academic Year
    • Change Password
    • Logout
Performance data not editable.

8️⃣ DATA FLOW (STUDENT SIDE)
Session Completed
↓
runAnalytics updated
↓
studentYearMetrics updated
↓
Portal reflects new summary
Portal never reads:
    • session logs
    • per-question timestamps
    • raw answer arrays
Only:
    • summary docs
    • per-run aggregated metrics

9️⃣ SCORE REPLACEMENT RULE (GLOBAL)
Everywhere in student portal:
Replace:
❌ Score
With:
✔ Raw Score %
✔ Accuracy %
Combined display example:
Raw: 72%   |   Accuracy: 81%
Never show raw marks cumulative across tests.

🔟 MOTIVATIONAL DESIGN STRATEGY
Student Portal must:
    • Highlight improvement
    • Show progress trends
    • Avoid harsh labels
    • Show next available test prominently
    • Encourage participation
Add dynamic banner:
“No test in progress. Next test available tomorrow at 5 PM.”
Or:
“You’ve completed 4 tests this month. Keep going!”

1️⃣1️⃣ PERFORMANCE REQUIREMENTS
    • Load < 300ms
    • Use summary docs only
    • Paginate completed tests
    • Lazy-load solution images
    • Do not load all solution images at once
    • Use CDN caching for images

1️⃣2️⃣ SECURITY RULES
    • Student cannot access Question Bank
    • Student cannot view other students’ data
    • Session access via signed token only
    • Archived solution data not accessible
    • No URL-based direct question access

1️⃣3️⃣ HOT–WARM–COLD ALIGNMENT
HOT:
    • Current year studentYearMetrics
    • Active runs
    • Current runAnalytics
WARM:
    • Completed runs (current year)
COLD:
    • Archived sessions in BigQuery
    • Only summary retained in Firestore
    • No solution access

FINAL STUDENT PORTAL SUMMARY
Student Portal now provides:
✔ Motivating dashboard
✔ Raw % + Accuracy % everywhere
✔ Testwise solution view (current year only)
✔ TutorialVideoLink integration
✔ SimulationLink integration
✔ Archived test summary only
✔ Behavior insight (L1+)
✔ Discipline tracking (L2+)
✔ Zero raw session exposure
✔ HOT–WARM–COLD aligned storage
The student experience becomes:
Operational → Reflective → Disciplined → Motivated


